### create a new booking
POST http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "room_id": 1,
  "visitor_name": "Jack Johnson",
  "visitor_email": "jack@example.com",
  "start_datetime": "2025-12-07T10:00:00Z",
  "end_datetime": "2025-12-07T11:00:00Z",
  "recurrence_rule": "",
  "status": "CONFIRMED"
}

### get all (filtered) bookings (needs admin access)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/

### update a booking 
PUT http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/2/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "start_datetime": "2025-12-04T14:00:00Z",
  "end_datetime": "2025-12-04T16:00:00Z",
  "recurrence_rule": ""
}

### update a booking (PATCH)
PATCH http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/4/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "start_datetime": "2025-12-08T14:00:00Z",
  "end_datetime": "2025-12-08T16:00:00Z",
  "recurrence_rule": ""
}

### delete a booking
DELETE http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/3/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "visitor_email": "alice@example.com",
  "cancel_reason": "Meeting postponed"
}

### delete a booking with wrong visitor_email
DELETE http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/2/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "visitor_email": "bob@example.com",
  "cancel_reason": "Meeting postponed"
}

### get a booking without visitor_email (needs admin access)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/2/

### get a booking with visitor_email
GET http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/2?visitor_email=alice@example.com

### get a booking with wrong visitor_email
GET http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/2?visitor_email=bob@example.com

### search bookings without visitor_email
GET http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/search

### search bookings with visitor_email
GET http://localhost:8000/api/bookings/search?visitor_email=bob@example.com